docs.abstract: Humans help train artificial intelligence, so someone may be listening to what you tell Siri, Google Assistant or Alexa. Here’s what to do if you have a problem with that.
docs.snippet: Humans help train artificial intelligence, so someone may be listening to what you tell Siri, Google Assistant or Alexa. Here’s what to do if you have a problem with that.
docs.lead_paragraph: Many of us ask the digital companions in our homes, whether it’s Amazon’s Alexa, Apple’s Siri or Google Assistant, to handle innocuous tasks like setting a timer and playing music.

headline.main: Hi, Alexa. How Do I Stop You From Listening In On Me?
headline.print_headline: Alexa, Please Stop Listening In on Me?

docs.abstract: Globalfoundries has accused T.S.M.C., a competitor in Taiwan, of infringing on 16 patents in a suit that could also affect companies like Apple and Google.
docs.snippet: Globalfoundries has accused T.S.M.C., a competitor in Taiwan, of infringing on 16 patents in a suit that could also affect companies like Apple and Google.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — One of the biggest semiconductor makers in the United States on Monday initiated a broad legal attack on Taiwan’s dominant chip manufacturer, the latest twist in a complex geopolitical battle over electronic components that could affect big chip users like Apple and Google.

headline.main: Lawsuit Over Computer Chips Invokes Trade War With China
headline.print_headline: U.S. Chip Maker Sues a Taiwanese Rival on Patents, Citing Trade War Issues

docs.abstract: Casio’s basic watches have barely changed in decades, a rare achievement as planned obsolescence is elevated to a corporate art form, our columnist says.
docs.snippet: Casio’s basic watches have barely changed in decades, a rare achievement as planned obsolescence is elevated to a corporate art form, our columnist says.
docs.lead_paragraph: IPhones haven’t been selling particularly well, Apple reported this summer, but its watches are becoming wildly popular. And no wonder.

headline.main: Apple’s Watch Is Smarter, but My Casio Keeps Getting the Job Done
headline.print_headline: It Reports the Time. It’s What I Want.

docs.abstract: Works by Nick Cave, Nathalie Djurberg, John Giorno and others have been choreographed into the landscape for an Apple-New Museum walking tour.
docs.snippet: Works by Nick Cave, Nathalie Djurberg, John Giorno and others have been choreographed into the landscape for an Apple-New Museum walking tour.
docs.lead_paragraph: Words appeared in the sky, the color of clouds, and then faded into a jumble of letters in the background. It was an ephemeral poem, with lines like “Catch the falling knife” visible for a few seconds through the portal of an iPhone pointed at the skyline above Central Park.

headline.main: Apple Transforms Central Park Into an Augmented Reality Gallery
headline.print_headline: iPhone Art Program In Central Park

docs.abstract: Top tech companies are rallying around the flag. How opportunistic of them.
docs.snippet: Top tech companies are rallying around the flag. How opportunistic of them.
docs.lead_paragraph: Not long ago, many leading technologists considered themselves too lofty and idealistic to concern themselves with the petty affairs of government. John Perry Barlow, a lion of the early internet, addressed his “Declaration of the Independence of Cyberspace” to the “governments of the industrial world,” saying that for him and his fellow netizens, these creaky institutions had “no moral right to rule us nor do you possess any methods of enforcement we have true reason to fear.”

headline.main: The Phony Patriots of Silicon Valley
headline.print_headline: The Phony Patriots of Silicon Valley

docs.abstract: Some of tech’s biggest names had founders in their teens. But new research shows that for fast-growing start-ups in the U.S., the average age was 45.
docs.snippet: Some of tech’s biggest names had founders in their teens. But new research shows that for fast-growing start-ups in the U.S., the average age was 45.
docs.lead_paragraph: It took an entrepreneur to reimagine the mundane home thermostat as an object of beauty — and then to make a fortune based on that vision.

headline.main: Founders of Successful Tech Companies Are Mostly Middle-Aged
headline.print_headline: High-Flying Tech Has a Touch of Gray

docs.abstract: America goes after Huawei, and Chinese consumers rally to buy from the company.
docs.snippet: America goes after Huawei, and Chinese consumers rally to buy from the company.
docs.lead_paragraph: BEIJING — Earlier this week the Chinese government aggressively devalued its currency — the clearest sign yet that it is hunkering down for a protracted fight with the United States over trade.

headline.main: Trump Has Succeeded. Now Lots of Chinese People Are Buying Huawei Phones.

docs.abstract: The Western Journal has had one of the biggest online audiences. But it now finds itself clashing with Silicon Valley tech giants. Here are highlights from a Times investigation.

headline.main: How a Conservative News Site Thrived on Facebook and Google

docs.abstract: The fast-growing Chinese company, blocked by the Trump administration from working with Google, announced plans for its own mobile operating system.
docs.snippet: The fast-growing Chinese company, blocked by the Trump administration from working with Google, announced plans for its own mobile operating system.
docs.lead_paragraph: DONGGUAN, China — Huawei, the Chinese technology giant, on Friday unveiled its own mobile operating system, Harmony, in an effort to ensure that its fast-growing smartphone business can survive the United States government’s clampdown on the firm.

headline.main: Huawei Unveils Harmony, Its Answer to Android, in Survival Bid
headline.print_headline: Huawei Fires Back at U.S. With Answer To Android
